<topic id="java_or_javascript">
  <title>Java or JavaScript?</title>
  <body>
    <p id="p_dnf_dgk_54b"><ph keyref="product"/> is a Java-based application and all of its APIs are Java-based. The
      entire user interface (buttons, views, dialog boxes) is built on top of the Java Swing
      architecture. The entire Javadoc API documentation is available here: <xref
        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/InstData/Editor/SDK/javadoc/" format="html" scope="external"
      />.</p>
    <p id="p_enf_dgk_54b">A <i>Workspace Access</i> plugin can be implemented either in Java or in JavaScript. Sample
      Java-based <b>Workspace Access</b> plugins can be found on the <xref
        href="https://github.com/topics/oxygen-standalone-plugin" format="html" scope="external"
        >Oxygen XML GitHub page</xref>. </p>
    <p id="p_fnf_dgk_54b">Sample JavaScript-based implementations can be found in this sample project: <xref
        href="https://github.com/oxygenxml/wsaccess-javascript-sample-plugins" format="html"
        scope="external"/>. The Rhino library is used to convert the JavaScript method calls to Java
      API calls: <xref
        href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Projects/Rhino/Scripting_Java"
        format="html" scope="external"/>.</p>
